   "source": [
    "# Wild Rift Player Churn Prediction\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook compares Random Forest, XGBoost, and LightGBM for player churn prediction, with a focus on early-session risk, cold-start behavior, and deployment-oriented evaluation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "e3147fbf",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import StratifiedKFold, cross_validate, cross_val_predict, train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\n",
    "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
    "from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import OneHotEncoder\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import (\n",
    "    accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score,\n",
    "    roc_auc_score, confusion_matrix, classification_report\n",
    ")\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
    "\n",
    "from xgboost import XGBClassifier\n",
    "from lightgbm import LGBMClassifier\n",
    "\n",
    "import shap\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_style(\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "pd.set_option(\"display.max_columns\", 200)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5b2907a3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Problem Statement\n",
    "\n",
    "Player churn is a critical business problem in mobile gaming because many users disengage within their first few sessions. In this setting, missing a true churner is often more costly than generating a moderate number of false positives. \n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook evaluates three machine learning approaches for churn prediction:\n",
    "- Random Forest\n",
    "- XGBoost\n",
    "- LightGBM\n",
    "\n",
    "The comparison focuses on:\n",
    "- AUC\n",
    "- precision\n",
    "- recall\n",
    "- F1-score\n",
    "- practical suitability for deployment"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9b8d19d8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Load Data\n",
    "\n",
    "Load the dataset and inspect the target column, missing values, and feature types."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "194afdcd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# change filename to your actual file\n",
    "file_path = \"predict_online_gaming_behavior.csv\"\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(file_path)\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "6a8001bf",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df.shape, df.columns.tolist()[:20]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "1c9e624c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# set your target column here\n",
    "TARGET = \"churn\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(df[TARGET].value_counts(dropna=False))\n",
    "print(df[TARGET].value_counts(normalize=True, dropna=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ae0718dd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Data Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "This section checks missing values, column types, and a few high-level characteristics of the dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "f612d7c8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df.info()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "2170256b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "missing_summary = df.isna().sum().sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    "missing_summary[missing_summary > 0].head(20)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "2f6cf6ed",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "categorical_cols = df.drop(columns=[TARGET]).select_dtypes(include=[\"object\", \"category\", \"bool\"]).columns.tolist()\n",
    "numeric_cols = df.drop(columns=[TARGET]).select_dtypes(include=[\"number\"]).columns.tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Categorical columns:\", len(categorical_cols))\n",
    "print(\"Numeric columns:\", len(numeric_cols))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7373f0bc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Prepare Features\n",
    "\n",
    "Split the dataset into features and target, then define preprocessing steps for numeric and categorical variables."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a3e978c2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X = df.drop(columns=[TARGET])\n",
    "y = df[TARGET]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "60ea9bbd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "numeric_transformer = Pipeline([\n",
    "    (\"imputer\", SimpleImputer(strategy=\"median\"))\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "categorical_transformer = Pipeline([\n",
    "    (\"imputer\", SimpleImputer(strategy=\"most_frequent\")),\n",
    "    (\"encoder\", OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown=\"ignore\"))\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "preprocessor = ColumnTransformer([\n",
    "    (\"num\", numeric_transformer, numeric_cols),\n",
    "    (\"cat\", categorical_transformer, categorical_cols)\n",
    "])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "87d0e5d5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Define Models\n",
    "\n",
    "Three models are compared using the same preprocessing pipeline and the same cross-validation setup."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "3618436c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "models = {\n",
    "    \"Random Forest\": RandomForestClassifier(\n",
    "        n_estimators=300,\n",
    "        max_depth=8,\n",
    "        random_state=42,\n",
    "        class_weight=\"balanced\"\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    \"XGBoost\": XGBClassifier(\n",
    "        n_estimators=300,\n",
    "        max_depth=6,\n",
    "        learning_rate=0.05,\n",
    "        subsample=0.9,\n",
    "        colsample_bytree=0.9,\n",
    "        eval_metric=\"logloss\",\n",
    "        random_state=42\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    \"LightGBM\": LGBMClassifier(\n",
    "        n_estimators=300,\n",
    "        learning_rate=0.05,\n",
    "        random_state=42,\n",
    "        class_weight=\"balanced\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "15b1765d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Cross-Validation Model Comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "This section compares the three models using stratified 10-fold cross-validation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "955a5d69",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cv = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=10, shuffle=True, random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "scoring = {\n",
    "    \"accuracy\": \"accuracy\",\n",
    "    \"precision\": \"precision\",\n",
    "    \"recall\": \"recall\",\n",
    "    \"f1\": \"f1\",\n",
    "    \"auc\": \"roc_auc\"\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for name, model in models.items():\n",
    "    pipe = Pipeline([\n",
    "        (\"prep\", preprocessor),\n",
    "        (\"model\", model)\n",
    "    ])\n",
    "    scores = cross_validate(pipe, X, y, cv=cv, scoring=scoring)\n",
    "    results.append({\n",
    "        \"Model\": name,\n",
    "        \"Accuracy\": scores[\"test_accuracy\"].mean(),\n",
    "        \"Precision\": scores[\"test_precision\"].mean(),\n",
    "        \"Recall\": scores[\"test_recall\"].mean(),\n",
    "        \"F1\": scores[\"test_f1\"].mean(),\n",
    "        \"AUC\": scores[\"test_auc\"].mean()\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "results_df = pd.DataFrame(results).sort_values(\"Recall\", ascending=False)\n",
    "results_df.round(3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f86e9d5a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Model Performance Visualization\n",
    "\n",
    "Plot model performance across key metrics."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "64716ab6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plot_df = results_df.melt(\n",
    "    id_vars=\"Model\",\n",
    "    value_vars=[\"Accuracy\", \"Precision\", \"Recall\", \"F1\"],\n",
    "    var_name=\"Metric\",\n",
    "    value_name=\"Score\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "sns.barplot(data=plot_df, x=\"Model\", y=\"Score\", hue=\"Metric\")\n",
    "plt.ylim(0.6, 1.0)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Model Performance Comparison Across Key Metrics\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "dbccbb03",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Final LightGBM Evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "Because LightGBM provides the strongest recall and good practical performance, it is selected for deeper inspection."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "8f7114f2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "lightgbm_pipe = Pipeline([\n",
    "    (\"prep\", preprocessor),\n",
    "    (\"model\", models[\"LightGBM\"])\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "pred = cross_val_predict(lightgbm_pipe, X, y, cv=cv, method=\"predict\")\n",
    "proba = cross_val_predict(lightgbm_pipe, X, y, cv=cv, method=\"predict_proba\")[:, 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "metrics_summary = {\n",
    "    \"Accuracy\": accuracy_score(y, pred),\n",
    "    \"Precision\": precision_score(y, pred),\n",
    "    \"Recall\": recall_score(y, pred),\n",
    "    \"F1\": f1_score(y, pred),\n",
    "    \"AUC\": roc_auc_score(y, proba)\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "pd.Series(metrics_summary).round(3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "6b6772f5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cm = confusion_matrix(y, pred)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 5))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt=\"d\", cmap=\"Blues\", xticklabels=[\"Stay\", \"Churn\"], yticklabels=[\"Stay\", \"Churn\"])\n",
    "plt.title(\"Confusion Matrix for LightGBM Churn Prediction\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Predicted\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Actual\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d8830d07",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Retention vs Churn by Session Count\n",
    "\n",
    "This view helps illustrate how churn is concentrated in the earliest sessions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "58253a23",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# replace with your real column name\n",
    "session_col = \"session_count\"\n",
    "\n",
    "tmp = df[[session_col, TARGET]].copy()\n",
    "tmp[session_col] = tmp[session_col].clip(upper=7)\n",
    "\n",
    "summary = (\n",
    "    tmp.groupby([session_col, TARGET])\n",
    "       .size()\n",
    "       .reset_index(name=\"count\")\n",
    ")\n",
    "summary[\"pct\"] = summary.groupby(session_col)[\"count\"].transform(lambda s: 100 * s / s.sum())\n",
    "\n",
    "pivot = summary.pivot(index=session_col, columns=TARGET, values=\"pct\").fillna(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "if 0 in pivot.columns and 1 in pivot.columns:\n",
    "    pivot = pivot.rename(columns={0: \"Stay\", 1: \"Churn\"})\n",
    "\n",
    "pivot[[col for col in [\"Churn\", \"Stay\"] if col in pivot.columns]].plot(\n",
    "    kind=\"bar\", figsize=(9, 5), color=[\"orange\", \"steelblue\"]\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Player Retention vs. Churn by Session Count\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Session Count\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Percentage of Players\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "646791d4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10. SHAP Explainability\n",
    "\n",
    "Use SHAP to understand which features contribute most to churn risk predictions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c725bbf7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X, y, test_size=0.2, stratify=y, random_state=42\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "lightgbm_pipe.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "X_test_processed = lightgbm_pipe.named_steps[\"prep\"].transform(X_test)\n",
    "lightgbm_model = lightgbm_pipe.named_steps[\"model\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "explainer = shap.TreeExplainer(lightgbm_model)\n",
    "shap_values = explainer.shap_values(X_test_processed)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "99fdaed3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "shap.summary_plot(shap_values, X_test_processed, show=False)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7bbdb479",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 11. Lifecycle Risk Heatmap\n",
    "\n",
