    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f389a7d3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 12. Key Findings\n",
    "\n",
    "Main conclusions from the analysis:\n",
    "\n",
    "- XGBoost produced the strongest AUC and precision.\n",
    "- LightGBM produced the strongest recall, which is more important for minimizing missed churners.\n",
    "- Random Forest is useful as an interpretable baseline but weaker for production deployment in this use case.\n",
    "- Cold-start sparsity, telemetry quality, and regional imbalance remain important risks beyond model choice alone.\n",
    "- LightGBM is the most practical deployment choice when balancing recall, speed, and operational fit."
   ]
  }
